Q: Buttons of irregular shape in QML A: <p>I think the approach is to use Item's <code>containmentMask</code> property. I have never used it myself, but the docs are <a href="https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-item.html#containmentMask-prop" rel="nofollow noreferrer">here</a>. You can define the mask using an image, or a Shape object, or even a function that you provide yourself. Here's an example using an image:</p>
<pre><code>Item {
    width: 200
    height: 200

    // Your irregular shape
    Image {
        id: shapeImage
        source: &quot;your-shape.png&quot; // PNG with transparent background
    }

    MouseArea {
        anchors.fill: parent
        containmentMask: shapeImage

        onClicked: {
            console.log(&quot;Clicked inside the shape!&quot;)
        }
    }
}
</code></pre>
